    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="809"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d809">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/11–1548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 16, 1948—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1634. No personnel should be evacuated US. Dept plans transfer large number to
                    other posts Far East[;] telegraph names personnel you intend evacuate from
                    Nanking Shanghai and other Chinese posts. Ref para 4 urtel 2216 Nov 15,
                        1948.<note n="62" xml:id="d809fn62">Not printed.</note> Paragraphs 1, 2 and
                    3 being answered separately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
